, may be written in polar form 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
y=e^{\frac{1}{2}\rho}e^{\frac{1}{2}\Phi}\left(x-e^{\frac{1}{2}\tau}e^{\frac{1}{2}\Theta}ae^{\frac{1}{2}\tau}e^{\frac{1}{2}\Theta^{\dagger}}\right)e^{\frac{1}{2}\rho}e^{\frac{1}{2}\Phi^{\dagger}}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
y=e^{\frac{1}{2}\left(\rho+\Phi\right)}\left(x-e^{\frac{1}{2}\left(\tau+\Theta\right)}ae^{\frac{1}{2}\left(\tau+\Theta\right)^{\dagger}}\right)e^{\frac{1}{2}\left(\rho+\Phi\right)^{\dagger}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since both 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau$
\end_inset

 and (restricted) 
\begin_inset Formula $\Theta$
\end_inset

